(42, 4, 22, 43, 6, 42, 42, 'Is not this Joseph’s son?', 'Connection of Jesus'' Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the question of Jesus'' identity as the son of Joseph. This connection highlights the skepticism surrounding his origins and the miraculous claims he makes.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 22, 44, 6, 10, 10, 'gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth', 'Connection of Wisdom and Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the remarkable nature of speech. In Luke, the people are amazed at Jesus'' words, while in Acts, the wisdom of Stephen''s speech is highlighted.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 22, 21, 12, 10, 11, 'gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth', 'Connection of Gracious Words', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on ''acceptable words'' in Ecclesiastes and the ''gracious words'' in Luke. Both passages reflect the significance of wise and truthful speech, suggesting a shared theme of the power and impact of words.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 22, 41, 6, 2, 3, 'Is not this Joseph’s son?', 'Reactions to Jesus'' Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the astonishment of the crowd at Jesus'' teachings and question his identity as ''Joseph’s son'' and ''the carpenter, the son of Mary.'' This connection highlights the theme of disbelief and familiarity with Jesus'' background leading to offense.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 22, 43, 7, 46, 46, 'gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth', 'Authority of Jesus'' Words', 'Both passages emphasize the remarkable nature of Jesus'' speech. In Luke, the crowd is amazed by his gracious words, while in John, the officers acknowledge that no one spoke like him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
